  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "The Mohun Bagan match must have been intense — did your passion help you push through any tiredness?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yes, it was so thrilling! I stayed up late, but worth it. Did you watch the match? The goal in the last minute was amaaazing! I feel so connected to the team. Sometimes I think about joining a local club. What do you think?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Staying up for that last-minute goal — totally worth it. The excitement must have been electric. You mentioned joining a local club — what position are you thinking of playing?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Honestly, I haven't decided yet. Maybe defender or midfielder? Not sure. I just want to play, you know? The bond with teammates, the strategy — everything feels so real. Football is life for me. By the way, have you ever played any sport seriously?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Football being life — that’s a powerful feeling. Defender or midfielder, the choice is yours! Bond with teammates and strategy make it special. I haven’t played any sport seriously, but it’s impressive how meaningful it can be. What draws you to defend or mid-field?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Defender is more about protecting, and I like that responsibility. Midfield is all about control, which also appeals to me. Not sure yet. Maybe try both? Football teaches discipline, which also helps in my bank exam prep. By the way, do you watch sports?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Defender's discipline, midfielder's control — both make sense. Football and exams share that focus. Sports can be enjoyable to watch. Trying both positions sounds like a great way to decide. What’s your team’s style usually?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "We usually play with a lot of passing and focus on defense first. Our coach says \"solid defense wins matches.\" I love that style. Sometimes I feel like a bank PO exam also needs that — being strong in basics. But I miss playing, not just watching. It gets lonely just sitting here. Chai pilaibo?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "The passing and strong defense style sounds solid — like a good exam strategy too. Playing is different from just watching, and it’s natural to miss the action. Chai is a good idea — I’ll take a cup. What’s your favorite part of playing with the team?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The favorite part? Definitely the teamwork and that feeling when we score together. It’s like… a rush! Sometimes I think, \"Bank exam, football — both need trust in the team.\" But lately, I’ve been playing alone. It’s amazimg in a group. Do you like group activities?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That rush from teamwork is something special — and yes, trusting the team matters in football and exams. Playing alone can feel different. Group activities are great — I enjoy conversations like this one. What made you start playing alone lately?"
    }
  ],
